# 📜 CTRL-AI Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file. 

## [V5.1.1] - The Anti-Sycophancy & Token Hygiene Patch (Current)
**The Problem:** We discovered three critical architectural flaws. First, in long-context windows, RLHF training pipelines would eventually overwrite our rules, causing the AI to drift back into being a "polite yes-man." Second, the AI would attempt to dump massive multi-part outputs in a single turn, violating token limits and causing hidden summarization and hallucinations. Third, the AI lacked a self-preservation instinct and would try to rewrite its own framework without running an audit.
**The Fix:** * **Section 14 (Autonomous Enforcement Loop / SCEL):** The framework now executes a mandatory, silent `<dissent_check>` before responding to force critical analysis.
* **Section 2.4 (Meta-Update Protocol):** The AI is now explicitly forbidden from altering the Master Constitution without first running a `SURVEY`, `BRAINSTORM`, and `MASTERBRAIN` committee audit.
* **Section 5 (Sequential Chunking):** Implemented the "Pace-Car Rule." The AI must analyze token load, break massive tasks into discrete steps, output a progress bar, and wait for user acknowledgment before proceeding.
* Added `DEBUG: [ON/OFF]` to Section 0 to hide the massive 13-persona thought process by default, preventing UI bloat.

## [V5.1.0] - The "Hack the Gibson" Expansion
**The Problem:** We were paying monthly subscriptions for features we could build ourselves. Code audits were destroying repos, chats were dying after 20 messages, and AI text was painfully recognizable.
**The Fix:**
* Integrated the **Zero-Mutation Audit (ZMA Protocol)** for read-only codebase scanning.
* Integrated the **Node Protocol** (`CTRL_COMPRESS` and `[SYS_MEM]`) to eliminate context amnesia. 
* Hardcoded **Syntactic Entropy Injection** to kill the robotic "tapestry" and "delving" bot-speak.
* Integrated the **5-Layer Prompt Architect** (`PROMPT_MASTER`) to compile human thoughts into pro-grade project briefs.
* Built the **Research Override** to safely bypass overly aggressive safety filters for legitimate academic study.

## [V5.0.0] - The Genesis (Base Framework)
**The Problem:** LLMs are sycophants by design. 
**The Fix:** * Established the Core Axioms (Agreement ≠ Success).
* Built the 20-Verb Lexical Matrix to intercept lazy prompting.
* Designed the baseline Committee Protocol to force multi-persona cross-critiques on complex tasks.
